    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="675"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3110</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Archangel</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 1, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>535. On receipt of your cable September 24, 5 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d675fn2"
                        >Not printed; see circular telegram, Sept. 20, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>,
                            <ref target="#pg_687">p. 687</ref>.</note> I sent copy thereof to
                    provisional government for its information: prompt reply was received approving
                    action and saying sovereign Archangel government expressed entire sympathy with
                    sentiments expressed by you and hoped that our noble aim would be accomplished
                    and— <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Government convinced that all nations acknowledging themselves morally
                            responsible to uphold human rights of mankind will unite their efforts
                            in supporting movement which America has initiated.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
